text: Wicomico County is a county located in the southeastern part of the U.S. state of Maryland, on the Delmarva Peninsula. As of the 2020 census, the county's population was 103,588. Its county seat is Salisbury. The county was named after the Wicomico River. It was created in 1867. == References == Category:19th-century establishments in Maryland Category:1867 establishments in the United States Category:Maryland counties
